speech: You may drop a course during the first five days of fall or spring semester, unless it is a fast track course. Course withdrawals (“W” grades) begin on the sixth day of the term, unless noted otherwise in the course schedule. The last day to withdraw date varies; it displays on students online schedule and on the course search details.

You don't have much time. Generally, you can drop a course during the first five days; and Course withdrawal - around 6, depending upon staff availability to here: http://century.custhelp.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/91
